        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-prose">
        <p>I started as a fine artist. Graduated in 2001 with a BFA from Southern Illinois University, then taught myself to code websites within a year. By 2002, I was writing HTML, CSS, and JavaScript alongside my design work, and I've been operating in both worlds ever since.</p>
        <p>Over 27 years, I've worked as a designer, a front-end developer, a creative manager, and a brand strategist. I've built websites, led creative teams, directed photo shoots, designed brand identity systems, and shipped multi-channel campaigns for Fortune 500 companies.</p>
        <p>But the work I'm most proud of is the work that didn't exist before I built it. At Grainger, where I've spent the last 13 years, I started noticing the same pattern: smart people stuck in slow workflows, spending hours on tasks that could be done in minutes with the right tool. So I started building those tools.</p>
        <p>I built a self-service flyer generator that turned a two-week design request into a five-minute task. I built an AI-powered metadata tool that automated hours of manual image tagging. I developed campaign identity systems, presented AI governance strategies to legal leadership, and helped position a 100-year-old industrial company to adopt emerging technology thoughtfully.</p>
        <p>Today I work at the intersection of design, front-end development, and AI. I identify problems that nobody else has thought to solve, and I build the tools that solve them. I also run Octave Design Studio, an independent practice that keeps me sharp across a range of creative challenges.</p>
